<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-10T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="272" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d272">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Rockhill</persName>
                                to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Abstract—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-10"><hi rend="italic">May 10,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Rockhill has seen T’ang Shao Yi. The latter says that the customs
                            revenue is already hypothecated and will not be touched; treaties and
                            pledges will be observed; the inspector-general will be an Englishman,
                            but China will have a right to control him, he being a servant of that
                            country.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>